The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, July 25: Steel minister Ram Vilas Paswan is understood to have asked state-run SAIL and private producers to hold prices for a few more months to help the government contain inflation, which is ruling at a 13-year high of 11.89 per cent.                             
	 Geneva, July 25: Troubled global trade talks showed signs of progress after crunch negotiations among seven key countries, ministers and officials said. There has been progress made, EU trade chief Peter Mandelson said.                            
	 London, July 25: Crude oil price hit a seven-week low on Friday, extending a decline that has knocked more than $20 off prices in two weeks. US crude was $2.09 lower at $123.40 by 1515 GMT and traded as low as $122.50, the lowest since June 5. Brent crude lost $2.05 to $124.39.                            
	 Mumbai, July 25: Reserve Bank is likely to finalise guidelines on mobile banking within two weeks that would enable banks to roll-out mobile-based payment services to their customers, a senior RBI official said.                            
	 New Delhi, July 25: Mobile operators added around 8.94 million mobile subscribers in June this year against 8.62 million in May, taking the total user base to 286.86 million in the country, said Trai.                                                                                                                         
